# Dashboard UI

## Overview
Build a Next.js 15+ TypeScript dashboard with Tailwind CSS for managing NextMavens Platform. Professional design with Inter font, neutral colors, no emojis/gradients. Integrate Supabase Auth, provide organizationsâ†’projects navigation, service redirects, and real-time notifications.

## Technical Approach
- Next.js 15 with App Router and TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS with professional color palette (slate/zinc)
- Supabase Auth for authentication
- Client-side Supabase client with RLS
- Realtime subscriptions for live updates
- Server Actions for mutations

## User Stories

### US-001: User Authentication
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [1, 7, 10]
**MCP Tools:** ["supabase", "chrome-devtools"]

As a user, I want to log in with email/password so that I can access my organizations and projects.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Login page at /login
- Email/password form with validation
- Session persisted
- Redirect to dashboard after login
- Logout functionality
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-002: Dashboard Home
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [1, 7]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a logged-in user, I want to see my organizations and projects on the dashboard so that I can navigate to my applications.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Display all organizations
- Display projects grouped by organization
- Quick actions (new project, new org)
- Statistics (total projects, active instances)
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-003: Organization Switcher
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [1, 7]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a user with multiple organizations, I want to switch between organizations so that I can focus on one context.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Dropdown or sidebar selector
- Shows current organization
- Lists all accessible organizations
- Updates context on selection
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-004: Project List View
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [1, 7]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a user, I want to see all projects in an organization with status indicators so that I can identify active/provisioning/suspended projects.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Table or card layout
- Status badges (active/provisioning/suspended)
- Quick links to Studio, logs, settings
- Filter by status
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-005: Create Project Modal
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [1, 7, 10]
**MCP Tools:** ["chrome-devtools"]

As an organization member, I want to create a new project so that I can deploy a new application.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Modal form with name, description, slug
- Slug auto-generated from name
- Validation for slug uniqueness
- Shows API keys after creation (one-time display)
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-006: Service Redirects
**Priority:** 2
**Maven Steps:** [1, 7]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a developer, I want quick links to external services so that I can access Studio, Evolution API, and other tools.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Links to Supabase Studio (per project)
- Links to Evolution API console
- Links to logs/monitoring
- Opens in new tab
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-007: API Key Management
**Priority:** 2
**Maven Steps:** [1, 7, 10]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a developer, I want to manage API keys so that I can rotate credentials and control access.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- List active API keys
- Show key prefix and last used
- Create new key (shows full value once)
- Revoke key
- Set expiration
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-008: Real-time Notifications
**Priority:** 2
**Maven Steps:** [1, 7]
**MCP Tools**: []

As a user, I want to receive real-time notifications so that I know about events affecting my projects.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Supabase Realtime subscription
- Toast notifications for events
- Events: deployment status, WhatsApp connect, errors
- Notification center history
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-009: Project Settings Page
**Priority:** 3
**Maven Steps:** [1, 7]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a project owner, I want to configure project settings so that I can customize behavior.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Edit project name/description
- Configure storage quota
- Set rate limits
- Danger zone: delete project
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-010: Team Management Page
**Priority:** 3
**Maven Steps:** [1, 7, 10]
**MCP Tools:** ["supabase"]

As an organization owner, I want to manage team members so that I can control access.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- List members with roles
- Invite new members
- Change member roles
- Remove members
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false
